Jasmine Guy https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jasmine_Guy 0 Jasmine Guy (born March 10, 1962) is an American actress, director, singer and dancer. Guy is known for her role as Dina in the 1988 film School Daze and as Whitley Gilbert-Wayne on the NBC Bill Cosby spin-off A Different World, which originally ran from 1987 to 1993. Guy won four consecutive NAACP Image Awards from 1990 through 1993 for Outstanding Lead Actress in a Comedy Series for her role on the show.
